  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-04-03 19:56 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Apr 3 Mid-Day: 5 trades, 4W/1L = 80% WR + V5b Tagging Live\n\n**Task:** P4 alpha \u2014 catch-up analysis for Apr 3 (backlog since 11:36)\n\n**Apr 3 Trading: 5 trades at 12h, 4W/1L = 80% WR**\n- 11h: 0 trades (BTC grinding up, bias positive, no contrarian opportunity)\n- 12h: 5 trades! BTC reversed slightly, bias went negative, bot fired.\n- 19h: 0 trades so far (bias positive again, BTC $66.8K trending up)\n- Balance: $894.97 \u2192 $871.70 (-$23). Trade math = +$10 net. ~$33 in unredeemed positions.\n\n**V5b TAGGING IS LIVE \u2014 First Validated Data:**\n| Trade | Bias | OBI | V5b Tag | Result |\n|-------|------|-----|---------|--------|\n| 12:12 | -29.2 | +0.32 | NORMAL | \u2705 WIN |\n| 12:37 | -69.8 | -0.49 | REDUCE_MILD_BEAR | \u2705 WIN |\n| 12:42 | -53.4 | +0.17 | NORMAL | \u2705 WIN |\n| 12:48 | -34.6 | **+1.00** | **REDUCE_STRONG_BULL** | \u274c LOSS |\n| 12:52 | -60.5 | +0.02 | NORMAL | \u2705 WIN |\n\n**The ONLY loss had OBI +0.998 (strongest bullish reading ever) \u2192 V5b tags it REDUCE.** V5b sizing would have halved this loss (-$5.88 instead of -$11.76).\n\n**V5a would block trade #1 (bias=-29.2) and trade #4 (bias=-34.6):**\n- Trade #1 was a WIN \u2192 V5a costs $5.88\n- Trade #4 was a LOSS \u2192 V5a saves $11.76\n- Net V5a impact today: +$5.88 saved\n\n**Regime: RANGE 0/6 all day (best possible).** But BTC trending up = bias positive at 11h and 19h. Only 12h had negative bias (BTC reversed briefly). Market structure favoring bulls today.\n\n**Next:** P1 copy intel\n\n---\n## 2026-04-03 11:36 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] Why Today's Session is Dry + Selectivity = Profit\n\n**Task:** P3 strategy \u2014 analyze why 11h has zero trades, validate selectivity thesis\n\n**Why No Trades (11:00-11:36):**\n- BTC grinding UP: $66,843 \u2192 $66,985 (+0.2%) in 30 min\n- Bias 71% positive (25/35 readings). Crowd bet